Category.Name: SequenceControl
Category.ToolTip: Contains parameters for configuring the sequencer.
Category.Description: Contains parameters for configuring the sequencer. The sequencer allows you to quickly change parameter settings during image acquisition by storing the desired settings in a sequence set. During image acquisition, the sequencer then executes the sequence sets in the order specified by you.

Boolean.Name: SequenceEnable
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables the sequencer.
Boolean.Description: Enables the sequencer.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceConfigurationMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets whether the sequencer can be configured.
Enumeration.Description: Sets whether the sequencer can be configured.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequencer can't be configured.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequencer can't be configured.

EnumEntry.Name: On
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The sequencer can be configured.
EnumEntry.Description: The sequencer can be configured.

Command.Name: SequenceAsyncRestart
Command.ToolTip: Enables asynchronous restart of the sequence set sequence.
Command.Description: Enables asynchronous restart of the sequence set sequence, starting with the sequence set that has the lowest index number. The restart is asynchronous to the camera's frame trigger. Only available in Auto and Controlled sequence advance mode.

Command.Name: SequenceAsyncAdvance
Command.ToolTip: Enables asynchronous advance from one sequence set to the next.
Command.Description: Enables asynchronous advance from one sequence set to the next. The advance is asynchronous to the camera's frame trigger. Only available in Controlled sequence advance mode.

Integer.Name: SequenceCurrentSet
Integer.ToolTip: Current sequence set.
Integer.Description: Current sequence set.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetTotalNumber
Integer.ToolTip: Total number of sequence sets in the sequence.
Integer.Description: Total number of sequence sets in the sequence.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetIndex
Integer.ToolTip: Index number of a sequence set.
Integer.Description: This number uniquely identifies a sequence set.

Command.Name: SequenceSetLoad
Command.ToolTip: Loads a sequence set.
Command.Description: Loads an existing sequence set to make it the current sequence set.

Command.Name: SequenceSetStore
Command.ToolTip: Stores the current sequence set.
Command.Description: Stores the current sequence set. Storing the current sequence set will overwrite any existing sequence set with the same index number. The sequence set is stored in the volatile memory and will therefore be lost if the camera is reset or if power is switched off.

Integer.Name: SequenceSetExecutions
Integer.ToolTip: Number of sequence set executions.
Integer.Description: Number of consecutive executions per sequence cycle of the selected sequence set. Only available in Auto sequence advance mode.

Category.Name: SequenceControlConfiguration
Category.ToolTip: Contains parameters for configuring the sequence set advance.
Category.Description: Contains parameters for configuring the sequence set advance. You can choose whether to let the sequencer cycle through the sequence sets automatically, or whether you want to control the sequence via an input line or software commands.

Enumeration.Name: SequenceAdvanceMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the sequence set advance mode.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the sequence set advance mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Auto
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The Auto sequence advance mode is selected.
EnumEntry.Description: The Auto sequence advance mode is selected. This mode is useful if you want to configure a fixed sequence which is repeated continuously. The advance from one sequence set to the next occurs automatically as frame triggers are received.

EnumEntry.Name: Controlled
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The Controlled sequence advance mode is selected.
EnumEntry.Description: The Controlled sequence advance mode is selected. This mode is useful if you want to configure a dynamic sequence which can be controlled via input line or software commands. The advance from one sequence set to the next proceeds in ascending sequence set index numbers according to the selected sequence control source.

EnumEntry.Name: FreeSelection
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The Free Selection sequence advance mode is selected.
EnumEntry.Description: The Free Selection sequence advance mode is selected. This mode is useful if you want to quickly change between freely selectable sequence sets without having to observe any particular order. You can use the input lines of your camera to determine the sequence.

When PTP is enabled, the Timestamp Control register can't be used to reset the timestamp. When PTP is enabled or disabled, the value of Timestamp Tick Frequency and Timestamp Value registers may change to reflect the new time domain.

Enumeration.Name: GevIEEE1588Status
Enumeration.ToolTip: Indicates the state of the IEEE 1588 clock.
Enumeration.Description: Indicates the state of the IEEE 1588 clock. Values of this field must match the IEEE 1588 PTP port state enumeration (INITIALIZING, FAULTY, DISABLED, LISTENING, PRE_MASTER, MASTER, PASSIVE, UNCALIBRATED, SLAVE).

EnumEntry.Name: Undefined
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in an undefined state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in an undefined state.

EnumEntry.Name: Initializing
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Initializing state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Initializing state. In this state, the port initializes its data sets, hardware, and communication facilities.

EnumEntry.Name: Faulty
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Faulty state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Faulty state. In this state, the port does not place any messages on its communication path. It discards all PTP messages received except for management messages.

EnumEntry.Name: Disabled
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Disabled state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Disabled state. In this state, the port does not place any messages on its communication path. It discards all PTP messages received except for management messages.

EnumEntry.Name: Listening
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Listening state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Listening state. In this state, the port is waiting for the so-called announceReceiptTimeout timeout to expire or to receive an Announce message from a master.

EnumEntry.Name: PreMaster
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the PreMaster state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the PreMaster state. In this state, the port behaves as if it were in the MASTER state except that some messages will not be placed.

EnumEntry.Name: Master
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Master state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Master state. In this state, the port is acting as the master port.

EnumEntry.Name: Passive
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Passive state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Passive state. In this state, the port is not acting as the master port nor does it synchronize with a master port.

EnumEntry.Name: Uncalibrated
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Uncalibrated state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Uncalibrated state. In this state, one or more master ports have been detected in the domain, the appropriate master port has been selected, and the local port is preparing to synchronize with the selected master port.

EnumEntry.Name: Slave
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The port is in the Slave state.
EnumEntry.Description: The port is in the Slave state. In this state, the port is synchronizing with the selected master port.

Enumeration.Description: Indicates the latched state of the IEEE 1588 clock. (The state must first be latched using the IEEE 1588 Latch command.) Integer.ToolTip: Low part of the latched IEEE 1588 parent clock ID of the camera.
Integer.Description: Low part of the latched IEEE 1588 parent clock ID of the camera.

Integer.Name: GevIEEE1588ParentClockIdHigh
Integer.ToolTip: High part of the latched IEEE 1588 parent clock ID of the camera.
Integer.Description: High part of the latched IEEE 1588 parent clock ID of the camera.

Integer.Name: GevSCPD

Integer.Description: Delay between the transmission of each packet on the selected stream channel. The delay is measured in ticks.

Integer.Name: GevSCFTD
Integer.ToolTip: Frame transmission delay on the selected stream channel.
Integer.Description: Frame transmission delay on the selected stream channel (in ticks). This value sets a delay before transmitting the acquired image.

Integer.Name: GevSCBWR
Integer.ToolTip: Percentage of the Ethernet bandwidth assigned to the camera to be held in reserve.
Integer.Description: Percentage of the Ethernet bandwidth assigned to the camera to be held in reserve for packet resends and for the transmission of control data between the camera and the host computer. The setting is expressed as a percentage of the Bandwidth Assigned parameter. For example, if the Bandwidth Assigned parameter indicates that 30 MBytes/s have been assigned to the camera and the Bandwidth Reserve parameter is set to 5 %, the bandwidth reserve will be 1.5 MBytes/s.

Integer.Name: GevSCBWRA
Integer.ToolTip: Multiplier for the Bandwidth Reserve parameter.
Integer.Description: Multiplier for the Bandwidth Reserve parameter. The multiplier is used to establish an extra pool of reserved bandwidth that can be used if an unusually large burst of packet resends is needed.

Integer.Name: GevSCBWA
Integer.ToolTip: Base bandwidth in bytes per second that will be used by the camera to transmit image and chunk feature data and to handle resends and control data transmissions.
Integer.Description: Base bandwidth in bytes per second that will be used by the camera to transmit image and chunk feature data and to handle resends and control data transmissions.

Integer.Name: GevSCDMT
Integer.ToolTip: Maximum amount of data (in bytes per second) that the camera can generate.
Integer.Description: Maximum amount of data (in bytes per second) that the camera can generate with its current settings under ideal conditions, i.e., unlimited bandwidth and no packet resends.

Integer.Name: GevSCDCT
Integer.ToolTip: Actual bandwidth (in bytes per second) that the camera will use to transmit image data and chunk data.
Integer.Description: Actual bandwidth (in bytes per second) that the camera will use to transmit image data and chunk data with the current settings for AOI, chunk features, and pixel format.

Integer.Name: GevSCFJM
Integer.ToolTip: Maximum amount of time (in ticks) that the next frame transmission could be delayed due to a burst of resends.
Integer.Description: Maximum amount of time (in ticks) that the next frame transmission could be delayed due to a burst of resends. If the Bandwidth Reserve Accumulation parameter is set to a high value, the camera can experience periods where there is a large burst of data resends. This burst of resends will delay the start of transmission of the next acquired image.

Category.Description: Contains parameters for controlling the Action Command feature which is used for triggering an action on multiple cameras at roughly the same time.

Integer.Name: NumberOfActionSignals
Integer.ToolTip: Number of separate action signals supported by the camera.
Integer.Description: Number of separate action signals supported by the camera. Determines how many action signals the camera can handle in parallel, i.e., how many different action commands can be configured on the camera.

Integer.Name: ActionCommandCount
Integer.ToolTip: Number of separate action signals supported by the camera.
Integer.Description: Number of separate action signals supported by the camera. Determines how many action signals the camera can handle in parallel, i.e., how many different action commands can be configured on the camera.

Integer.Name: ActionSelector
Integer.ToolTip: Action command to be configured.
Integer.Description: Action command to be configured.

Integer.Name: ActionDeviceKey
Integer.ToolTip: Device key used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Device key used to authorize the execution of an action command. If the action device key in the camera and the action device key in the protocol message are identical, the camera will execute the corresponding action.

Integer.Name: ActionGroupKey
Integer.ToolTip: Group key used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Group key used to define a group of cameras on which action commands can be executed.

Integer.Name: ActionGroupMask
Integer.ToolTip: Group mask used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Group mask used to filter out a sub-group of cameras belonging to a group of cameras. The cameras belonging to a sub-group execute an action at the same time. The filtering is done using a logical bitwise AND operation on the group mask number of the action command and the group mask number of a camera. If both binary numbers have at least one common bit set to 1 (i.e., the result of the AND operation is non-zero), the corresponding camera belongs to the sub-group.
